metadata.name: rive #362
metadata.description:
Starting with a repeatable system of colors and/or triangles typically seen in geometric abstraction, rive employs generative art to break/split/rive those patterns–and the comfort we find in them–in slight, seemingly unintentional ways.  With each subsequent split, our comfort fades as the artwork is shredded into barely recognizable fragments of a once carefully orchestrated pattern.

Not all rivings are created equal; some are subtle and barely visible while others are acute and violent.  

What holds it together is what breaks it apart.  

created using triangles and p5js

rive
abstractment, 2022

___________________________

Functionality:
Press ‘p’ to save as a png.
Press 0-9 to render at varying degrees of quality. 0 to 9 (highest quality, ~15k x ~15k, depending on the dimensions).  The window background will change colors when completed rendering.
Press ⬆️ (arrow up) to increase pixel density by 0.5.
Press ⬇️ (arrow down) to decrease pixel density by 0.5.

metadata.name: THE400FLIPS #110
metadata.description:
The more they flip. The more you’ll make.

p5.js –> Blockchain


Controls:

[s] save as PNG.
[a] render alternate higher resolution artwork (takes a few seconds).
[z] save alternate artwork as PNG.


Artist note:

Primary royalties are split 95-5% between artist and The Processing Foundation.

Secondary royalties go to the minters (99.9% of the 15%).

The preview thumbnails don’t do justice to the artworks. Please run the code to appreciate them better. Also, remember to check the alternate higher resolution renders using [a].

Some preview thumbnails might look slightly different to the artwork seen when running the code. This is due to the resolution difference between the capture module and the live code on your device. 

Please get in touch in the event of a blank preview thumbnail. 

Made in p5.js and rendered in webGL. Tested on Chrome and Safari.

metadata.name: Hash Tiles #26
metadata.description:
Is life random? Are beauties created by chance?
All these many species of creatures with diversity in appearance, behavior and temperament, how beautiful and romantic together interpret life and being.
Forms and colors in small and large dimensions, together and in different forms, create a great image of concepts and love.
A generation learns from another generation and a culture from another culture, and in one way or another it personalizes and continues its path, and in the end, it transmits its findings to another generation and culture.
Sometimes these effects fade, and sometimes they mutate and manifest themselves in future generations and cultures.
They may be contradictory in appearance and in comparison, but in general they play an attractive role.
"Human beings are members of a whole
In creation of one essence and soul "
Is life an accident?

metadata.name: Rhythms #399
metadata.description:
"Routines, patterns, cadence.
Events, turns, chaos.
Predictable lives,
split-second dramas."

This project is inspired by the delicate balance between daily habits and life-turning points.
There's structure in the flow. There's awe in the silence.

"Rhythms" invites you to reflect on the beautiful complexity that fills our vital experience, on the millions of tiny details that bring texture to our journey causing balance or disruption.

-

Key Features:
- 12 color palettes: Determines colors used on the artwork
- 3 Orientation modes (square, portrait, landscape): Portrait and landscape are rare
- 6 Alignment Types: Determines lines' distribution pattern

Secondary features provide additional variation.

Enter live mode and press "s" to download high resolution image ( 5940x5940 px ).

-

50% of secondary market royalties go to minters.
Coded in p5js, with love.

metadata.name: Particularization #10
metadata.description:
“Particularization” is the seventh collection released as a part of NeoMent's "Abandoned Reality" series.

All concepts can be viewed from different levels. You can focus on the details, leaving out the generalized result but understanding the finer points. Or you could emphasize the concept as a whole, comprehending it well overall but missing out on the specifics. It's impossible to choose both, you have to figure out which approach works best for each scenario.

metadata.name: Arrows Between Emotions #65
metadata.description:
The project “Arrows Between Emotions” was formed with a concern to present this transformation in an artist and code developer, making the logic appear through precise and well-defined forms, but that the stage was really of emotions through freer curves involving aligned with accentuated movements in directions of straight or oblique ascents and even in more circular or decadent processes that are part of the journey of the wheel of life of art and the artist.


The process of the work involved the construction of a background to receive the shapes and colors. I used an algorithm that generated a distribution of noise across the screen, with its coloring related to the shapes in the search for a pleasant composition. Then came the objective forms, setting the stage, finally, for the flow of emotions through the agglutinated and dispersed curves soaked in colors in a game of shadow and light, presenting the depth and movement of the creation process and the orientation to which it takes. all the strength of this walk.

Press 's' key in live mode to save in png.

@pixelflowart, May 2022

metadata.name: Valley of Empty Future #49
metadata.description:
*translated from drone swarm operator 51b13*
Preliminary analysis of the planet's atmosphere suggest an increased concentration of carbon monoxide, consistent with temperature readings.
No fauna or flora detected on immediate surface. Even though soil spectroscopy confirm presence of organic compounds, samples must be collected in order to have definitive results.

Scouts have confirmed, trough x-ray and radar imaging, sprawling areas of artificial environments. High density of buildings suggest an intricate and highly developed societal structure, with only it's tallest buildings piercing trough the meters deep silicate dust covering most of the area. It intrigues me why build so high, would these be religious monuments to be seen by all, for their exuberance? Immediately forwarding digital reconstruction of the -cities?- for Cosmic Sociologists to further speculate on their purposes.

////

On fullscreen view, press P to download a 1920*2560 PNG

Made in Cables.gl
